2.  **Bypassing/Manipulating Logic:**
    *   **Force Success/Failure:** A powerful technique would be to intercept `fail` and, instead of calling `this.fail(outputParams)`, call `this.success(outputParams)` or vice-versa. This could trick the application into believing a critical update succeeded when it failed, or vice versa, potentially leading to a persistent vulnerable mini-app or a denial of service if an update is perpetually "failing."
